Description: Something you don't see everyday! A hot pink strat body loaded with 2 dimarzio's and a pearly gates Seymour Duncan in the neck. I bought this body years ago and it was a made in England strat body that was black I stripped the paint and sprayed it hot pink via rattlecan(terrible blemishes everywhere). Added a few s*itty decals hacked up a hot pink Jeanne pickguard(50 dollar destruction) and inserted a mid 80's paf pro pink dimarzio in the middle position an even older pink dimarzio (different shade of pink) what would be the precursor for the d-activator in the bridge, and a newer pink (almost rasberry colored) Seymour Duncan pearly gates neck pickup in the neck position. The output on those 3 pickups is like 8,9,13 (starting in neck if my memory serves me correctly). I'm basically selling the body for what I think the three pickups are worth......The electronics are good cts pots I'm pretty sure and it's all wired and works great.....the body is special to me as I've owned it for as long as I've played and it served as my platform where I learned how to mod and solder and it has been through like 100 different makeovers.... The neck pocket is a little deep so I added it's own neckplate to the neck pocket and it allows the use of any normal strat neck now....I had a warmoth neck on this guy forever....will need a bridge as it's bridge was taken for another project a 2-1/8 spaced mim bridge fit perfectly....to round it off through some hot pink decals on it just for kicks, ps the body is very heavy no idea what wood....all said and done it's a great body that will turn some heads and am selling it for less than j think the pickups are worth.... Let me know if you have any questions. -Mark As always my auctions are free shipping to the lower US lower 48 via UPS. PayPal only. No returns!!!! All my stuff is used and I described them to my best ability!!!!! Make an offer!!!!!
Title: Hot Pink Strat Stratocaster Body Custom Dimarzio Partscaster
